data.text:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. (WZTV) -- Pekka Rinne, Ice hockey goaltender for the Nashville Predators was announced to be on injured reserve Saturday.

According to the tweet of theDigital manager and producer of the NHL Predators, Miroslav Svoboda from Milwaukee Admirals onSaturday night in the game against Edmonton Oilers. Once the Predators return home, goaltender Troy Grosenick will replace Svoboda.

Rinne left the Friday night game early after colliding with player Kevin Fiala from the Calgary Flames. Rinne will be on reserve for the next three games.
